# safeSHEE Environment Variables

## Twilio SMS Configuration (Optional)

To enable real SMS notifications via Twilio:

1. Create a Twilio account at https://www.twilio.com
2. Get your credentials from Twilio Console:
   - Account SID
   - Auth Token
   - Phone Number (from Phone Numbers section)

3. Create a `.env` file in the `backend/` directory:

```
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your_account_sid_here
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your_auth_token_here
TWILIO_PHONE=+1234567890
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key_here
PORT=5000
```

4. Restart backend server

## Without Twilio

If you don't have Twilio configured, the app will:
- Use a mock SMS service
- Log SMS messages to console and database
- Continue working normally (no SMS actually sent)

## Testing SMS (Development)

### Test POST to send SMS:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/sos/test/sms \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
    "message": "Test SMS"
  }'
```

### View Mock SMS Log:
```bash
curl http://localhost:5000/sos/test/sms-log \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN"
```

## WebSocket Configuration

WebSocket is automatically enabled when backend starts.
- Runs on same port as HTTP server (5000)
- Frontend connects automatically on load
- Real-time events: new_alert, status_change, location_update

No additional config needed!
